r size=1> Recently I posted requesting those that are plane capable and not part of an alliance to post their names.  However, I was forced to cancel PoA this weekend because no clerics.<br>
<br>
Do we even have enough people for plane raids?  This is a serious question.  I can't post for raids if no one is going to show up.  KGC is constantly booked with guilds that want to do these raids, cancelling at the last minute is very unprofessional.<br>
<br>
And if it's a matter of we do have enough people, but people only going to do raids that their armor drops in.  Well fine then, I will do the same thing, and seeing I have my armor, I don't see the need to do PoF or PoH anymore.  No sense in wasting my time.  I don't get rewarded for this.  In fact I had to miss out on alot of Large targets with The Watchmen alliance due to the politics of percieved double dipping.<br>
<br>
If it's just the plane raids we are short on people for because of alliances being reformed from the split.   Then no problem, we can deal with the cards dealt to us.  I can still run raids for Vellious, after all CoG is open to everyone.  Just the planes have politics.<br>
<br>
However, based on the last turn out of Vellious, I even question that.  It's a shame too, everyone missed out on a great opportunity.  I hear people whining oh, necropolis is only for Uber Guilds.  But then I form one, and I find myself doing a 3 hour recruiting spree to get the event off the ground.  Least some really excellent drops for the people that had the patience to wait.  And 80% of people below 50, only two people 54, and one 55+.<br>
<br>
Well, here's the bottom line.  If we can't get the support for the raids, I can't do the raids. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#FFFFCC><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/uhaemish.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Haemish</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/globalBlack.gif BORDER=0 HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10></span><br> <span class=usertitle>ezOP</span><br> <font color=#8E9173>(2/24/01 12:47:52 am)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://www.godwin.com/sd/haemish.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Are we even a functioning entity anymore?</span><hr size=1> Zellex,<br>
<br>
I have not been on EQ much all week, trying to take a break to avoid raid burnout. However, I think you hit the nail right on the head for the problem. You asked only non-guilded and non-alliance people onto the PoA raid. <br>
<br>
Personally, and I've stated this a few times, I don't see a problem with alliance people going on planes raids with the CoG. If this is seen by some as double-dipping, too bad, look at the KGC guidelines. It does allow for people to be recruited from other guilds when needed to fill out the roster. We have more than enough people, but seems that we are getting short on clerics especially. <br>
<br>
I would say this. If you want to run the planes raids and we're getting short on some class, ask members of your guild, your friends, members of any guild. I asked for clerics the night of the last SB raid and from 1 cleric to start we got 3 for the whole night. <br>
<br>
The other way to make this work is to start sending out a press release every time we book a plane calling for signups. Many may not check this board very often. <br>
<br>
The CoG has and CAN still do planes raids. If it takes every person on the raid begging their guild's clerics to come, that's what it takes. It may be a pain in the ass but it's the rules we work with.<br>
<br>
Haemish <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#CBC6B1><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/umigg.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Migg</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#8E9173>(2/25/01 12:51:59 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Are we even a functioning entity anymore?</span><hr size=1> Zellex<br>
